\f2\b 01_Tango_Style:
\f0\b0  A popular style for icons on the Linux computing system is one called 'Tango'. This diagram comes from their web site and describes how this style should be accomplished and clearly defines it's look and feel and also includes a color palette to use. All though the colors are not iron clad.\
\
Note the thick outer line, contrasting with the thinner inner lines, subtle use of blended colors (gradients) and a nice drop-shadow. My icons will match this style so this is all part of the research I am doing upfront before I even start.
